1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 60 O.S. 2021, Section 651, as
3 amended by Section 1, Chapter 421, O.S.L. 2025 (60 O.S. Supp. 2025,
4 Section 651), is amended to read as follows:
5 Section 651. As used in the Uniform Unclaimed Property Act,
6 unless the context otherwise requires:
7 1. “Apparent owner” means the person whose name appears on the
8 records of the holder as the person entitled to property held,
9 issued, or owing by the holder;
10 2. “Attorney General” means the chief legal officer of this
11 state;
12 3. “Banking organization” means any bank, trust company,
13 savings bank, safe deposit company, private banker, or any
14 organization defined by other law as a bank or banking organization;
15 4. “Business association” means a non-public nonpublic
16 corporation, joint-stock company, investment company, business
17 trust, partnership, or association for business purposes of two or
18 more individuals whether or not for profit, including a banking
19 organization, financial organization, insurance company, or utility;
20 5. “Claimant” means a person who claims an interest in
21 unclaimed property in the custody of the State Treasurer;
22 6. “Claimant’s representative” means a person who has been
23 hired by a claimant to file an unclaimed property claim on behalf of
24
Req. No. 3942 Page 2

1 a cl aimant pursuant to a written agreement, including a duly
2 executed power of attorney;
3 7. “Domicile” means the state of incorporation of a corporation
4 and the state of the principal place of business of an
5 unincorporated person;
6 8. “Financial organization” means a savings and loan
7 association, building and loan association, or credit union;
8 9. “Holder” means a person, wherever organized or domiciled,
9 who is:
10 a. in possession of property belonging to another,
11 b. a trustee, or
12 c. indebted to another on an obligation;
13 10. “Insurance company” means an association, corporation,
14 fraternal or mutual benefit organization, whether or not for profit,
15 which is engaged in providing insurance coverage, including
16 accidental, burial, casualty, credit life, contract performance,
17 dental, fidelity, fire, health, hospitalization, illness, life
18 (including including endowments and annuities) annuities,
19 malpractice, marine, mortgage, surety, and wage protection
20 insurance;
21 11. “Intangible property” includes:
22 a. money, checks, drafts, deposits, interest, dividends,
23 and income,
24
Req. No. 3942 Page 3

1 b. credit balances, customer overpayments, security
2 deposits, refunds, credit memos, unpaid wages, unused
3 airline tickets, and unidentified remittances,
4 c. stocks and other intangible ownership interests in
5 business associations,
6 d. monies deposited to redeem stocks, bonds, coupons, and
7 other securities, or to make distributions,
8 e. amounts due and payable under the terms of insurance
9 policies, and
10 f. amounts distributable from a trust or custodial fund
11 established under a plan to provide health, welfare,
12 pension, vacation, severance, retirement, death, stock
13 purchase, profit sharing, employee savings,
14 supplemental unemployment insurance, education or
15 similar benefits;
16 12. “Last-known address” means a description of the location of
17 the apparent owner sufficient for the purpose of the delivery of
18 mail;
19 13. “Memorandum” shall include a mark, symbol or statement
20 indicating knowledge of or interest in funds on deposit;
21 14. “Mineral proceeds” includes:
22 a. all obligations to pay mineral proceeds resulting from
23 the production and sale of minerals, including net
24 revenue interest, royalties, overriding royalties,
Req. No. 3942 Page 4

1 production payments, and payments under joint
2 operating agreements, and
3 b. all obligations for the acquisition and retention of a
4 mineral lease, including bonuses, delay rentals, shut-
5 in royalties, and minimum royalties;
6 15. “Museum” means an institution which is located in this
7 state and operated by a nonprofit corporation or a public agency
8 primarily for educational, scientific, historic preservation or
9 aesthetic purposes, and which owns, borrows, cares for, exhibits,
10 studies, archives, or catalogues property. “Museum” Museum
11 includes, but is not limited to, historical societies, historical
12 sites or landmarks, parks, monuments and libraries;
13 16. “Owner” means a depositor in the case of a deposit, a
14 beneficiary in case of a trust other than a deposit in trust, a
15 creditor, claimant, or payee in the case of other intangible
16 property, or a person having a legal or equitable interest in
17 property or the person’s legal representative. Where more than one
18 person is an owner, the property shall not be presumed abandoned
19 unless it has remained unclaimed by all of its owners for the
20 periods hereinafter prescribed;
21 17. “Person” means an individual, business association, state
22 or other government, governmental subdivision or agency, public
23 corporation, public authority, estate, trust, two or more persons
24
Req. No. 3942 Page 5

1 havi ng a joint or common interest, or any other legal or commercial
2 entity;
3 18. “State” means any state, district, commonwealth, territory,
4 insular possession, or other area subject to the legislative
5 authority of the United States;
6 19. “State Treasurer” or “Treasurer” means the duly elected and
7 acting State Treasurer of Oklahoma;
8 20. “Tax Commission” or “Commission” means the Oklahoma Tax
9 Commission;
10 21. “Utility” means a person who owns or operates for public
11 use any plant, equipment, property, franchise, or license for the
12 transmission of communications, or the production, storage,
13 transmission, sale, delivery, or furnishing of electricity, water,
14 steam, or gas; and
15 22. “Written agreement” means a legally binding document
16 between a claimant and the claimant’s representative outlining the
17 terms and conditions of the agreement. It provides a clear record
18 of the agreement, specifying each party’s rights, responsibilities,
19 and obligations, which authorizes the claimant’s representative to
20 claim and recover unclaimed property in the custody of the State
21 Treasurer on behalf of the claimant. The agreement may include an
22 authorization that directs the State Treasurer to remit payment of
23 fees due to the claimant’s representative subject to the provisions
24 of this title.
